HEADWORD: Plater
<hw>Plat"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who plates or
coats articles with gold or silver; <as>as, a silver
<ex>plater</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A machine for calendering paper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plater</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Plater
<hw>Plat"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Horse Racing)</fld>
<def>A horse that runs chiefly in plate, esp. selling-plate, races;
hence, an inferior race horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plateresque</ent>⟦br⟧
